        "text": "In 1965, with [[Derek Bryan (diplomat)]], a retired diplomat whom he first met in China, Needham established the [[Society for Anglo-Chinese Understanding]], which for some years provided the only way for the British to visit the People's Republic of China. On a visit to China in 1964 he was met by Zhou Enlai, but on a visit in 1972 he was deeply depressed by the changes under the [[Cultural Revolution]]."
